FBIS3-10982 "drlat051_b_94002" FBIS-LAT-94-051 Document Type:Daily Report 15 Mar 1994 Haiti International Group in UN Opposes Sanctions FL1503231694 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1145 GMT 15 Mar 94 FL1503231694 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole Language: French Article Type:BFN [Text] The Group of Latin American and Caribbean countries, Grolacc, on 14 March, expressed to the UN Security Council its opposition to a resolution bill that would impose a total trade embargo on Haiti until democracy returns to the country. According to diplomatic sources, Grolacc's position received the support of several members of the Council, notably Spain, Nigeria, and Djibouti. In a new attempt to harmonize the efforts of the international community, mediator Dante Caputo invited representatives of the four countries, the so-called Friends of Haiti -- the United States, Canada, France, and Venezuela -- to hold a high-level meeting on the Haitian question in New York on 17 or 18 March.
